    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. u said it was a \"strategic miscalculation\" though. isn't that a pretty strong take? i've seen some people argue that any intervention that doesn't end in a stable democracy is basically a failure by definition. do u think that's a fair way to judge it, or is there more to it than just whether the country ended up stable?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
